@undef_obj @mohit @TheSwaminator After investigating CLI source code I decided to use the resources.addCfnResource method to manually add the AWS::Lambda::Permission resources+properties to create the invoke permissions, but this isn't documented anywhere

@undef_obj @mohit @TheSwaminator The override.ts seems to want the resources.lambdaConfigPermissions property but it's typed to accept entries of lambda.cfnPermission which isn't possible to instantiate that class because override.ts doesn't allow importing the cdk / logic is executed inside a VM  & no fs access

@undef_obj @mohit @TheSwaminator based on the issues threads I saw people need a way to set their custom trigger configurations via the override.ts but there's no way of obtaining the standard environmental info like the lambda name/lambda arn without a hacky work round to require the amplify-meta.json file

@undef_obj @mohit @TheSwaminator @undef_obj The latest amplify v7 asks to migrate our auth category when working with it viaAmplify CLI. The override.ts documentation's a bit opaque when looking to translate all the customizations made in the cloudformation template which now's deleted as part of the migration

I'll add that AWS support did not know what to do about the new Auth category override.ts customizations but I found a way *Jurassic Park*
